p2
VVoice of the violin
p3
sVnews
p4
VViolinist Chembai C.K. Venkitaraman, a faculty member of Chembai Memorial Music College, Palakkad, displayed his musical lineage at a concert at Vithunni Saneswara Temple recently. An heir to the legendary Chembai Vaidyanadhabhagavathar bani, Venkitaraman, charmed rasikas with his unique bowing technique. Venkitaraman was accompanied by his disciple Preethi Unni on the violin, Guruvayoor Sanoj on the mridangam and Gopi Nadalaya on the morsing.Rhythmic pieceA rhythmic Nattakkurinchi Adi tala varnam of Sreerangam Rangaswamippillai, &#8216;Chalamela' had the Poorvanga sung in two speeds and Utharanga in second speed. Dikshitar's &#8216;Mahaganapathim' in Natta, which was embellished with a spirited swarasanchara followed.Tyagaraja's &#8216;Ramabhakthi samprajya' in Sudhabangala (Adi tala) had Venkitaraman bringing out the sahithyabhava and structural aesthetics of the piece. An exquisite portrayal of Reethigowla was followed by a Subbarayasasthrikal composition &#8216;Janani ninuvina,' which began with the Anupallavi.Bhava-laden elaborationA fast-paced &#8216;Bandureethikolu' of Tyagaraja in Hamsanada was followed by Preethi's bhava-laden elaboration of Varali. Dikshitar's &#8216;Mamava meenakshi' set to Misrachappu tala came next.Expressive niraval at &#8216;Syame&#8230;,' with glides and alternate playing of swara segments by both the violinists was pleasing.Gopalakrishna Bharathi's &#8216;Sabhapathikku verudaivam Samanama' in Abhogi was embellished with cascading manodharmaswara.Swati's &#8216;Narasimha mamava Bhagavan' in Arabhi (Khadhachappu tala) led to the highlight of the evening, an erudite rendition of Kamboji, with the violinist bringing to fore its salient features. Dikshitar's &#8216;Marakathavalli' in Adi tala (two kala) had clear sangathis that was decorated with impressive swarasancharas in two speeds. It culminated into scintillating korvais. The tani was good.The latter half of the concert had a Kapi alapana for &#8216;Ennathavam seithanai' of Papanasam Sivan and a ragamalika of Lalithadasar &#8216;Bhakthasanjeevana' in ragas Sindhubhairavi, Mohanam and Surutti. Venkitaraman concluded his recital with the popular Dhanasree thillana of Swati Tirunal and Mangalam. The concert was organised by Swathi Sangeetha Sabha, Palakkad.
